<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3331"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3331-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3331">Text messaging from voice&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4612-4049">azaleahs</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">5 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">If you could talk to your phone and have it send a text message you could access data without being put on hold. <br/><br/>The resulting information could be texted back to your blackberry and saved.<br/><br/>You could send text messages much quicker, even if you have a fingering disability. <br/><br/>A library could receive a line of text messages and originate answers in text easily as well. <br/><br/>Combined with the fact that many cell phone companies provide unlimited texting for a real small amount of money and you can see it should have been done long ago.<br/></div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3331" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3331', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2236&topicID=3331')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3331"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2236">Making Data More Accessible</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3331"></div>
