<div id="Idea_3236"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3236-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3236">A change in the "Open Government Dialogue"&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4612-4049">azaleahs</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">5 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Provide a record of how many positive votes and how many negative votes each idea gets. Otherwise an idea that gets a thousand positives and a thousand negatives may be ignored or seen as zero support when it really received quite a bit of support. <br/><br/>If you won the vote of only half the people while the other half hated your guts you might still win the election. Lots of Presidents don't do that well.</div>
